Supporters of Thika Town MP Alice Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a and those of her two rivals clashed on Wednesday during President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s visit.The supporters of Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a and those of Patrick Wainaina and Morris Mburu engaged in a shouting match, when the President addressed residents.Uhuru reopened the Volkswagen Kenya production line at the Kenya Vehicle Manufactures factory.Each group wanted to speak to the President.Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a was heckled by her rivals&rsquo; supporters when she was given a chance to speak, forcing her to cut short her speech. &ldquo;We support the President&rsquo;s reelection, but Ng&rsquo;ang&rsquo;a must go. We need change in Thika and never will we vote blindly again,&rdquo; a supporter said.Uhuru calmed the crowd. Governor William Kabogo called for the arrest of Mbita MP Millie Odhiambo for &ldquo;insulting&rdquo; the President. He said Kiambu leaders and residents will not allow her to disrespect Uhuru.